1.Create a S3 bucket and put objects in bucket through local PC using AWS CLI
Sol) Step 1: Create IAM User with S3 Full Access


Log in to the AWS Management Console.

Go to Services > IAM.
 
 
Click Users > Add user.

Enter username and select Programmatic access.
 
 
Click Next: Permissions
Search for AmazonS3FullAccess policy and attach it.

 
 
Click Next and then Create user.
Download or copy the Access Key ID and Secret Access Key.


Step 2: Install and Configure AWS CLI on Local PC Open PowerShell or Command Prompt.
Run the command:
aws configure
Enter the Access Key ID, Secret Access Key, region (e.g., us-east-1), and output format (default or json).

 
Step 3: Verify AWS CLI Connection Run:
aws s3 ls
You should see a list of existing S3 buckets (or none if none exist).

 


Step 4: Create an S3 Bucket Using AWS CLI Run the command:
aws s3api create-bucket --bucket your-unique-bucket-name --region us-east-1

 
Verify creation by refreshing S3 buckets list in AWS Console or running: aws s3 ls
 
 





Step 5: Upload Files to S3 Bucket Using AWS Console Open your S3 bucket in AWS Console.
 
 
Click Upload.

Add files and complete the upload.

 
 




Step 6: Verify Objects in S3 Bucket Using AWS CLI Run:
aws s3 ls s3://aws-cli-s3-snehitha --recursive --human-readable â€“summarize This lists all objects in the bucket with details.
 
 
